    "body": "Hey @intellent â€” this is a great question. Since Electron uses NodeJS, you can use the `fs` module in NodeJS to access the filesystem. For your game, it might make sense to check to see if the user has a custom JSON file, and fall back to the default one in the app. Alternatively, you could copy the JSON file into /user/appdata the first time it's launched so they can see it and edit it there.\n\nThe code might look something like this:\n\n```\nvar app = require('electron').app;\nvar fs = require('fs');\nvar path = require('path');\n\nvar customJSONPath = path.join(app.getPath('userData'), 'my-levels.json')\n\nif fs.existsSync(customJSONPath)\n   // load from this path\nelse\n   // load from default path\n```\n"
